09/09/2007
VIDIN, Bulgaria -- During a visit to the town of Vidin Saturday (September 8th), Bulgarian Foreign Minister Ivailo Kalfin said Bulgaria is seeking to introduce a visa-free regime with neighbouring countries.
He said a draft agreement on the issue has been prepared, but needs official approval by the European Commission.
(News.bg, BNR, MIA, A1 TV - 08/09/07)
